Aim :- To interface a push button as a digital input and control an LED by toggling itsstate in each valid button press.
Apparatus :- STM32 Nucleo-F446RE Development Board ; USB Type-A to Mini-B Cable ; STM32CubeIDE ; STM32CubeMX
Theory :- The STM32f446RE microcontroller provides multiple GPIO ports that can be configured as a digital output to contol the onboard LED(LD2), and 
       pin PC13 is configured as a digital input connected to the user button. The push Button works on active-low logic,meaning the pin reads LOW 
       when pressed and HIGH when released. Using HAL functions such as HAL_GPIO_ReadPin() and HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(), the LED state is toggled whenever
      a valid button press is detected. A small delay is added to handle basuc debouncing and prevent multiple unwanted toggles.
Procedure :-
    1.  Open STM32CubeMX and acess the MCU Selector
    2.  Select STM32F446RE and start the project    
    3.  Configure PA5 as GPIO Output(LED) and PC13 as GPIO Input(Push Button)
    4.  Select RCC clock source (BYPASS).
    5.  Configure clock settings.
    6.  Enter project name and select STM32CubeIDE.
    7.  Generate code and open project.
    8.  Open main.c file.
    9.  Write code using HAL_GPIO_Pin() , HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(), HAL_delay() inside the loop 
    10. Build project(no error)
    11. Connect board using USB cable
    12. Debug and resume
    13. Press push button and observe LED toggle.
